xpressed just in terms of sine.<br><br>So why are there are more than one? =
 For the most part, it is because trigonometry has been really important to=
 engineering and navigation for thousands of years.  Obviously, pocket calc=
ulators that are powerful enough to compute trig functions have only been a=
round for a small fraction of that time, so people got by with tables of tr=
ig values and doing any extra work by hand.  So, if you were solving a tria=
